    },
    {
      "id": "t8",
      "tag": "p",
      "text": "The short answer: YouTube pays between"
    },
    {
      "id": "t9",
      "tag": "strong",
      "text": "$3 and $6 per 1,000 views"
    },
    {
      "id": "t10",
      "tag": "p",
      "text": "on average through its RPM (Revenue Per Mille) model. But that average hides enormous variation — a finance channel might earn $15 per 1,000 views while a gaming channel earns $2."
    },
    {
      "id": "t11",
      "tag": "strong",
      "text": "Key distinction:"
    },
    {
      "id": "t12",
      "tag": "p",
      "text": "CPM is what advertisers pay YouTube. RPM is what you, the creator, actually receive — roughly 55% of CPM after YouTube's revenue share."
    },
