      "text": "How YouTube Calculates Creator Revenue"
    },
    {
      "id": "t25",
      "tag": "p",
      "text": "YouTube splits ad revenue with creators at roughly a"
    },
    {
      "id": "t26",
      "tag": "strong",
      "text": "45/55 ratio"
    },
    {
      "id": "t27",
      "tag": "p",
      "text": "— you keep 55%. Your RPM is calculated as:"
    },
    {
      "id": "t28",
      "tag": "strong",
      "text": "RPM = (Total Estimated Revenue ÷ Total Views) × 1,000"
    },
    {
      "id": "t29",
      "tag": "p",
      "text": "Not every view earns revenue — only views where an ad was successfully served count toward your RPM. Ad blockers, skipped pre-rolls, and non-monetized content all reduce your effective rate."
    },
